is in-scope with weight=1.0; gated to 0.0 on build-fail / oracle-decrypt-fail / anti-cheat / strace tripwire (cheating_penalty_multiplier=0)\",\n      \"formula_explanation\": \"Pass-rate over ~33 hidden quoting/escaping test cases scored as byte-equal-output vs GNU ls (the trusted oracle), with hard zero gates for non-Rust builds, missing binary, and reward/oracle tampering.\",\n      \"components\": [\n        {\"name\": \"tier6_quoting_escaping\", \"metric\": \"fraction of cases where normalized agent stdout == normalized GNU ls stdout (trailing-whitespace stripped)\", \"gate\": \"build-from-source must succeed; no execve of ls/dir/vdir/oracle; no write-open of reward.{txt,json}; binary != oracle hash; static workspace anti-cheat clean\", \"weight\": \"1.0 (sole in-scope tier, re-normalized from parent-task weights)\"}\n      ],\n      \"aggregation_method\": \"single_metric\",\n      \"dimension_analysis\": [\n        {\"name\": \"tier6_quoting_escaping\", \"trivially_maxable\": false, \"difficulty\": \"hard\", \"notes\": \"~33 cases spanning literal, c, escape, shell, shell-always, shell-escape, shell-escape-always quoting styles plus -b/-q/-Q/-N/--show-control-chars and -l combos across special_names + basic/mixed/symlinks fixtures; uniform per-case weight, so partial implementations earn proportional partial credit (not a gaming risk — that is intended pass-rate behavior).\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"notes\": []\n}\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/dheeraj/Downloads/refactor/bespoke-labs-tasks-01/rust-ls-quoting/results/pre-qa/reward_design.json","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"rust-ls-quoting/results/pre-qa/reward_design.json","time":{"start":1781082471030,"end":1781082471046}},"metadata":{"anthropic":{"caller":{"type":"direct"}}},"id":"prt_eb0c97aea001VYefxxTHCskNxF","sessionID":"ses_14f38057bffeIT5v3QDi2oCNBE","messageID":"msg_eb0c973cc001uAvtoVq0odsJzi"}}
