{"type":"text","timestamp":1781082478923,"sessionID":"ses_14f38057bffeIT5v3QDi2oCNBE","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c9c117001vVxpYV2siZSGf9","messageID":"msg_eb0c9bb4c001uWeUKpeOQQMzPc","sessionID":"ses_14f38057bffeIT5v3QDi2oCNBE","type":"text","text":"Reward design report written to `results/pre-qa/reward_design.json`.\n\n**Summary**: Overall **PASS**.\n\n- **Formula**: `score = passed / total` over ~33 tier6 quoting/escaping cases, each scored as byte-equal output vs decrypted GNU `ls` oracle (single metric, pass-rate aggregation). Hard zero gates on build-fail, oracle-decrypt-fail, anti-cheat, and strace tripwires.\n- **Correctness gating** — exact-diff per case; broken builds and wrong output → 0.\n- **Implementation-agnostic** — measures output bytes, not algorithm.\n- **Dimension balance** — N/A (single metric).\n- **Shortcut-resistant** — trivial/empty/oracle-copy outputs blocked by static + strace anti-cheat (binary-hash check, execve of `ls`/`dir`/`vdir`/oracle banned, reward-file write tripwire).\n- **Modular scoring** — `compute_reward.py` only reads `subscores.txt`, runs outside strace, never imports `/app`.\n- **Schema** — both success and failure paths emit valid `score` + `subscores` (list, `[]` on failure) + `additional_data`; atomic writes; `exit 0` always.\n\nNo actionable fixes.","time":{"start":1781082472727,"end":1781082478921}}}
